<specimenCount id="2EA88FB7FFC3FFCE174EFBF4FE105D14" box="[270,450,1109,1135]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
):
</emphasis>
One adult specimen (MHNCUP/REP 318, formerly UP-MHNFCP-017432; 
<figureCitation id="A09558BBFFC3FFCE136DFBF7FA5D5D0A" box="[1325,1423,1110,1137]" captionStart="FIGURE S" captionStartId="68.[151,250,1069,1093]" captionTargetBox="[170,1416,164,1044]" captionTargetId="figure-33@68.[170,1416,164,1044]" captionTargetPageId="68" captionText="FIGURE S53. Specimen of Atheris cf. squamigera (MHNCUP/REP 318), from Golungo Alto. Photo by Bruna Santos." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5454089" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5454089/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. S53</figureCitation>
), collected from Golungo Alto [-9.13333º, 14.76667º, 
<quantity id="FF56E9DBFFC3FFCE14BCFBDBFC945DEF" box="[764,838,1146,1172]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.659999999999999" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="m" value="666.0">666 m</quantity>
a.s.l.] 
<collectingRegion id="FA6A8ADCFFC3FFCE15D9FBDBFB625DEF" box="[921,1200,1146,1172]" country="Angola" name="Kwanza Norte" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Kwanza Norte Province</collectingRegion>
, date unknown; 
<specimenCount id="2EA88FB7FFC3FFCE1334FBDBFF1D5DC3" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="adult">one adult</specimenCount>
specimen (MHNCUP/REP 319, formerly UP-MHNFCP-017413), collected from unknown locality, date unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="70B417B5FFC3FFCE1687FB44FED05FCB" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3811443EFFC3FFCE1687FB44FED05FCB" blockId="27.[151,1437,1109,1712]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC3FFCE1687FB44FE805D84" bold="true" box="[199,338,1253,1279]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFC3FFCE1717FB47FDE35C7B" box="[343,561,1254,1280]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Atheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="squamigera">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC3FFCE1717FB47FDE35C7B" box="[343,561,1254,1280]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Atheris squamigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to West and Central Africa, with a distribution ranging from 
<collectingCountry id="40B904AEFFC3FFCE1308FB47FA4E5C7B" box="[1352,1436,1254,1280]" name="Nigeria" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="40B904AEFFC3FFCE16F5FAABFF2C5C5F" box="[181,254,1290,1316]" name="Kenya" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Kenya</collectingCountry>
and from 
<collectingCountry id="40B904AEFFC3FFCE1735FAABFE085C5F" box="[373,474,1290,1316]" name="Tanzania" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
to northern 
<collectingCountry id="40B904AEFFC3FFCE1426FAABFD6A5C5F" box="[614,696,1290,1316]" name="Angola" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Angola</collectingCountry>
(including the 
<collectingCountry id="40B904AEFFC3FFCE1526FAABFC115C5F" box="[870,963,1290,1316]" name="Angola" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Cabinda</collectingCountry>
enclave) (
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFC3FFCE127AFAABFAF05C5F" author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[1082,1314,1290,1316]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC3FFCE12E6FAAAFB0D5C5F" box="[1190,1247,1290,1316]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFC3FFCE136FFAABFE815C33" author="Chippaux, J. - P. &amp; Jackson, K." pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refId="ref36575" refString="Chippaux, J. - P. &amp; Jackson, K. (2019) Snakes of Central and Western Africa. Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore, 448 pp." type="book" year="2019">Chippaux &amp; Jackson 2019</bibRefCitation>
). The taxonomic status of other putative valid forms traditionally associated with 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFC3FFCE12B1FA8FFA475C33" box="[1265,1429,1326,1352]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Atheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="squamigera">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC3FFCE12B1FA8FFA475C33" box="[1265,1429,1326,1352]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">A. squamigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFC3FFCE16FBFAF3FD8B5C17" authority="Mocquard, 1887" authorityName="Mocquard" authorityYear="1887" box="[187,601,1362,1388]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Atheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anisolepis">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC3FFCE16FBFAF3FE595C17" box="[187,395,1362,1388]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Atheris anisolepis</emphasis>
Mocquard, 1887
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFC3FFCE142AFAF3FC3A5C17" authority="Boettger, 1887" authorityName="Boettger" authorityYear="1887" box="[618,1000,1362,1388]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Atheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laeviceps">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC3FFCE142AFAF3FCE25C17" box="[618,816,1362,1388]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Atheris laeviceps</emphasis>
Boettger, 1887
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFC3FFCE1259FAF3FA4A5C16" authority="Rochebrune 1885" authorityName="Rochebrune" authorityYear="1885" box="[1049,1432,1362,1389]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Atheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lucani">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC3FFCE1259FAF3FB6E5C17" box="[1049,1212,1362,1388]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Atheris lucani</emphasis>
Rochebrune 1885
</taxonomicName>
, remains problematic (see 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFC3FFCE17FAFAD7FD705CEB" author="Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Tolley, K. A. &amp; Marques, M. P. &amp; Heinicke, M. P. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[442,674,1398,1424]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref35999" refString="Ceriaco, L. M. P., Tolley, K. A., Marques, M. P., Heinicke, M. P. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2020 c) A dwarf among giants: phylogenetic position of the elusive Angolan Adder (Bitis heraldica) and biogeographic affinities of Angolan Afromontane regions. African Journal of Herpetology, 69 (1), 1 - 11. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 21564574.2020.1782484" type="journal article" year="2020">
Ceríaco 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC3FFCE1459FAD6FD9E5CEB" box="[537,588,1398,1424]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al</emphasis>
. 2020c
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFC3FFCE14EEFAD7FC4E5CEB" author="Collet, M. &amp; Trape, J. - F." box="[686,924,1398,1424]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="27 - 40" refId="ref36607" refString="Collet, M. &amp; Trape, J. - F. (2020) Une nouvelle espece du genre Atheris Cope, 1862, de la province de l'Eiquateur en Republique Democratique du Congo (Squamata: Viperidae). Bulletin de la Societe Herpetologique de France, 173, 27 - 40." type="journal article" year="2020">Collet &amp; Trape 2020</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFC3FFCE15E8FAD7FB665CEB" author="Spawls, S. &amp; Branch, W. R." box="[936,1204,1398,1424]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refId="ref40292" refString="Spawls, S. &amp; Branch, W. R. (2020) The Dangerous Snakes of Africa. Bloomsbury Wildlife, London, 336 pp." type="book" year="2020">Spawls &amp; Branch 2020</bibRefCitation>
). This is particularly relevant to the study of Angolan populations of 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFC3FFCE1487FA3BFC1F5CCF" box="[711,973,1434,1460]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Atheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="squamigera">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC3FFCE1487FA3BFCCA5CCF" box="[711,792,1434,1460]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Atheris</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC3FFCE1509FA3AFC1F5CCF" box="[841,973,1435,1460]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">squamigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as most of these forms were described from very close to the northern Angolan border, and the diagnostic characters of both are not clearly defined yet. A detailed morphological review of the group is currently underway (Ceríaco 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC3FFCE15A0FA42FBCA5C87" box="[992,1048,1506,1532]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al.</emphasis>
unpublished data). 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFC3FFCE12B3FA43FA4E5C86" author="Ferreira, J. B." box="[1267,1436,1506,1533]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="159 - 171" refId="ref37198" refString="Ferreira, J. B. (1906) Algumas especies novas ou pouco conhecidas de amphibios e reptis de Angola (Coleccao Newton - 1903 - 1904). Jornal de Sciencias Mathematicas Physicas e Naturaes, Segunda Serie, 7 (26), 159 - 171." type="journal article" year="1906">Ferreira (1906)</bibRefCitation>
reported an adult specimen of “ 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFC3FFCE17B3F9A7FD125F5B" authorityName="Welch" authorityYear="1994" box="[499,704,1542,1568]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Atheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="squamiger">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC3FFCE17B3F9A7FD125F5B" box="[499,704,1542,1568]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Atheris squamiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” from “Golungo Alto”, that upon analysis we find likely to match MHNCUP/REP 318, although the specimen had no locality attached. This species was first described from the 
<typeStatus id="E715FA9CFFC3FFCE16D7F9EFFF155F13" box="[151,199,1614,1640]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">type</typeStatus>
locality “near the river Gaboon, 
<collectingCountry id="40B904AEFFC3FFCE1477F9EFFD595F13" box="[567,651,1614,1640]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Guinea</collectingCountry>
” (Hallowell “1854” 1855). 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFC3FFCE1580F9EFFB635F13" author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[960,1201,1614,1640]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC3FFCE1268F9EEFBB25F13" box="[1064,1120,1614,1640]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
denoted the need for further study regarding this species, to assess whether it constitutes a species complex or is subject to geographical variation.
</paragraph>
